The paper proposes an end-to-end image compression framework based on convolutional neural network, which involves feature description neural network, standard image codec, post-processing neural network, and virtual codec neural network. The paper focuses on resolving the problem of non-differentiability of the quantization function in the standard codec, which is a common issue in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves advanced learning algorithms and optimization techniques, which are related to cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the compression rate-distortion trade-off, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory).
